<P N="4">4. Do&s;t thou thus provoke the Lord to jealou&s;ie, art thou &s;tronger than He? God is wi&s;e in heart, and mighty in &s;trength, who hath hardened his heart again&s;t Him, and hath pro&s;pered? <HI>Joh</HI> 9.4. <HI>There is no wi&s;dom, nor under&s;tanding again&s;t the Lord.</HI> Prov. 21.30. If therefore thou wilt not &s;earch the Scriptures, nor hear the voice of God, nor cry for the Spirit to convince thee of thy unbelief; and to put forth the exceeding greatne&s;s of his power to make thee willing to come as as an ungodly lo&s;t &s;inner to Chri&s;t? If the Kingdom of Heaven do not &s;uffer violence, if thou do&s;t not pre&s;s into it and take it by force; I thee te&s;tify to thee from the God of hea|ven, that the door of mercy will &s;hortly be &s;hut, thou &s;halt hereafter &s;tand with|out,
