<P>Que&s;t. 2. I <HI>Be&s;eech you, &s;ince my pre&s;ent condition is &s;o dreadful, as Gods Word reveals it, tell me if there be any hopes for &s;uch a Sinner, and what cour&s;e I mu&s;t take?</HI></P>
<P><HI>An&s;w,</HI> When the Keeper of the Pri&s;on asked <HI>Paul</HI> and <HI>Silas,</HI> Sirs, What mu&s;t I do, to be &s;aved? They &s;aid, <HI>Bel<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">eve on the Lord Je&s;us Christ, and thou &s;hal<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter"> be &s;aved, and thy hou&s;e, Act.</HI> 16, 30, 31. Therefore immediately under the means of Grace,
