<P N="3">3. Long in&s;atiably to be found in Chri&s;t, not having thine own Righteou&s;ne&s;s, which is of the Law, but the Righteou&s;ne&s;s which is through the Faith of Chri&s;t, <HI>Phil.</HI> 3&middot; Never expect to be healed by the Law: but through the Righteou&s;ne&s;s of Chri&s;t without the deeds of the Law: for the Law can only wound thee, and give thee the knowledge of &s;in, <HI>Rom.</HI> 3.20, and there it leaves thee in a helple&s;s &amp; peri&s;h|ing condition; it only works wrath, and Cur&s;eth thee, and Judgeth and Condemn|eth thee. It is very u&s;ual with troubled
